  "text": "Kubernetes watch event delivery trace from etcd to client:\n\n1. **etcd Event Generation (etcd-io/etcd)**:\n   - `server/mvcc/watcher.go` defines the `watchStream` struct (lines 97-109) which maintains a collection of watchers sharing one streaming channel. The `watchStream.Watch()` method (lines 112-140) registers watchers on the etcd MVCC store and returns events through the `Chan()` method.\n   - `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/watch.go` defines the `serverWatchStream` struct (lines 121-150+) which manages the server-side gRPC stream. It receives watch events from `mvcc.WatchStream` (field at line 134) and forwards them to gRPC clients.\n\n2. **Kubernetes API Server Watch Cache (kubernetes/kubernetes)**:\n   - `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/cacher.go` defines the `Cacher` struct (lines 245+) which implements storage.Interface. The `Cacher.Watch()` method (lines 515-693) creates watch requests and manages event distribution to multiple clients. It receives events from the underlying etcd storage and processes them through the `dispatchEvents()` method (lines 1033-1092).\n   - `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/watch_cache.go` defines the `watchCache` struct (lines 91-157) which is a sliding window event buffer. It stores watched events in a circular buffer and provides methods to query events by resource version.\n   - `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/cache_watcher.go` defines the `cacheWatcher` struct (lines 53-88) which implements the watch.Interface. Each client watch gets a cacheWatcher instance with input and result channels (lines 54-55). The `ResultChan()` method (lines 115-118) returns the channel where events are sent to clients.\n\n3. **Kubernetes Client Watch (kubernetes/client-go)**:\n   - `tools/cache/reflector.go` defines the `Reflector` struct (lines 59-122) which watches a specified resource. The `ListAndWatch()` method (lines 348-377) initiates the watch by calling `r.listerWatcher.Watch()` (line 451). The Reflector then receives events through the watch interface and processes them via `handleWatch()` function, updating the store with each received event.\n\n**Event Flow Summary**:\netcd MVCC watchers (watchStream) → etcd gRPC Watch RPC (serverWatchStream) → Kubernetes API Server (Cacher receives stream) → Cacher.dispatchEvents() distributes to watchCache → individual cacheWatchers send to their result channels → Reflector receives events via ListAndWatch and updates local cache/store."
}

